    <abstract>
      <t>Redundancy protection is a method of service protection by sending
   copies of the same packets of one flow over multiple paths, which
   includes packet replicaiton, elimination and ordering.  This document
   defines SRv6 header(SRH) extensions to support redundancy protection.</t>
    </abstract>
